==CT virtual bronchoscopy==
This technique uses data from multiple [[CT]] scans to create a three dimensional (3D) image. This allows doctors to see what is going on without having to operate.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0720048X02002954 |title=CT virtual bronchoscopy in the evaluation of children with suspected foreign body aspiration |first= Mithat|last=Haliloglu et.al. |work=European Journal of Radiology |year=2003 |accessdate=28 March 2013}}</ref>
